item.title: The Dead Triplets
item.description: This post could about music theory and rhythm, such as the triplet guitar riffs in invincible or even the lyrics from the whole chart busting album. But this about a single chapter, in a single from a book from the swamp from which I quote liberally. It is probably already a more influential book than I realize. As monks say, the soul is wet (thus presumably messy) and a dry soul is lacking life.
